physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Physical examination revealed a 1x1.5 cm diameter capillary haemangioma on the forehead, frontal bossing and broad forehead, hypertelorism, posteriorly rotated low-set ears, long philtrum, micrognathia, anteverted nares, pectus excavatum deformity, right thumb agenesis, wrist contractures, clinodactyly, lumbosacral hypertrichosis, and a sacral dimple. Auscultation revealed a 2/6 systolic murmur on the left sternal border. Other systemic examinations suggested no abnormalities.
